The “heaps” of “chains” in Joe’s shop link to Marley’s chain. The
chains could symbolise how the thieves and Marley are trapped
in their lifestyles — the thieves are bound by poverty, and Marley
is bound in eternal punishment. However, you could also argue
that, like Marley, the thieves’ callous actions are contributing to
their own “chain” that they will have to bear in the afterlife.
